Nigeria’s first choice goalkeeper, Maduka Okoye, is looking forward to another three points and a clean sheet when the Super Eagles face Sudan’s Falcons of Jediane in their second group D match at the Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) in Cameroon tomorrow. The Sparta Rotterdam shot stopper had a dream AFCON debut, recording a clean sheet as he shut-out Liverpool’s Mohamed Salah and his Pharaohs teammates in Nigeria win over Egypt on Tuesday with one of the major highlights of the game being when the 22-year-old denied Salah in a one-on-one situation in the second half.   NIGERIA vs. Sudan Eguavoen fancies  Eagles chances     Nigeria vs Sudan:  Super Eagles  set  to clip Falcons’ wings     Troost-Ekong looks beyond semifinal berth   “It feels great, I think I need to give thanks to the team because we played very well. I am very happy to get the clean sheet on Tuesday,” he said. “First of all I am looking forward to another three points, a clean sheet is always good, it is a sign of good defending and compact teamwork. - Advertisement - “We have placed ourselves on a high pedestal. We have to put it in our minds that this is just the first game. We still have six more games to go to win the cup.”